cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.GT. 

This paper deals with energy management in wireless sensor networks, which involves communication, information theory, and control systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a game-theoretic formulation to solve the optimization problem, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper presents numerical simulations to validate the proposed approach, which could be considered as cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
